licenses, and the Belgian datasets that are most wanted to be opened up next.\r\n[sessions day=open-belgium-2]','Day 1: Open Belgium','','inherit','closed','open','','162-revision-v1','','','2013-12-17 08:24:39','2013-12-17 08:24:39','',162,'http://www.datadays.eu/162-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(293,2,'2013-12-17 08:56:39','2013-12-17 08:56:39','','Dr. Julia Glidden and panel: Open Transport','','inherit','closed','open','','267-autosave-v1','','','2013-12-17 08:56:39','2013-12-17 08:56:39','',267,'http://www.datadays.eu/267-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(294,2,'2013-12-17 09:08:00','2013-12-17 09:08:00','','Dr. Julia Glidden','','publish','closed','closed','','dr-julia-glidden','','','2013-12-19 12:07:18','2013-12-19 12:07:18','',0,'http://www.datadays.eu/?post_type=dd-speaker&#038;p=294',1,'dd-speaker','',0),(295,2,'2013-12-17 09:08:36','2013-12-17 09:08:36','','julia-glidden','','inherit','closed','open','','julia-glidden','','','2013-12-17 09:08:36','2013-12-17 09:08:36','',294,'http://www.datadays.eu/wp-content/uploads/2013/12/julia-glidden.jpg',0,'attachment','image/jpeg',0),(296,2,'2013-12-17 10:24:45','2013-12-17 10:24:45','<b>Data Days – Tickets &amp; registration</b>\r\n\r\nData Days is a three-day conference in Ghent, Belgium, exploring how open data is changing the way the Public Sector innovates and delivers services:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Open Belgium\" href=\"http://www.datadays.eu/open-belgium/\" target=\"_blank\">Open Belgium (17 Feb)</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Open Europe\" href=\"http://www.datadays.eu/open-europe/\" target=\"_blank\">Open Europe (18 Feb)</a></li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Open World\" href=\"http://www.datadays.eu/open-world/\" target=\"_blank\">Open World (19 Feb)</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<b>Data Days registration</b>\r\n<div>\r\n\r\nData Days is a three-day conference, allowing you to follow certain modules or chose a full conference ticket. Notice that you must use a recent browser!\r\n\r\nAll pricing is in Euros and includes VAT and handling fees. No additional charges will be made.\r\n\r\n1 Day ticket:  100 Euro\r\n\r\n2 Days ticket:  160 Euro\r\n\r\n3 Days ticket: 200 Euro\r\n\r\n</div>\r\n<div><b>Multiple tickets</b></div>\r\nYou will be able to purchase multiple tickets in one registration procedure. Be advised that you will need to confirm both contact details and information on which sessions each participant will attend.\r\n\r\n<b>Press &amp; media accreditation</b>\r\n\r\nAs a journalist or media professional, you can apply for a media accreditation <a title=\"Media accreditation\" href=\"mailto:sarah.buelens@bz.vlaanderen.be\" target=\"_blank\">here </a>, allowing for full access to the conference and the possibility to put in interview requests.\r\n\r\n<b>Payment methods</b>\r\n\r\nOnline ticket payments are handled <b>100% securely</b> and through all the common payment methods: Visa, Mastercard, Paypal, Bancontact, American Express, Homebanking (Dexia netbanking, ING Homepay and KBC Online), iDEAL (Holland) of bank transfer.\r\n\r\n<b>Invoices</b>\r\n\r\nYou will receive a confirmation e-mail stating the details of your purchase and the total amount paid upon registration. The ticketing system does not provide invoices automatically, though.\r\n\r\nIf you would need an invoice, you can <a title=\"invoice\" href=\"mailto:jessica.vandendries@bz.vlaanderen.be\" target=\"_blank\">send us</a> the ticket details, so we can prepare an invoice for you. Don’t forget to mention you VAT number!\r\n\r\n<b>Refund policy</b>\r\n\r\nAllData Days tickets are non-refundable, however we make it very easy to transfer your ticket to another person.\r\n\r\nTo transfer your ticket, simply contact our <a title=\"Ticket transfer\" href=\"mailto:sarah.buelens@bz.vlaanderen.be\" target=\"_blank\">help desk</a> with your transfer request and our awesome support team will help you.','Registration','','inherit','closed','open','','213-revision-v1','','','2013-12-17 10:24:45','2013-12-17 10:24:45','',213,'http://www.datadays.eu/213-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(297,2,'2013-12-17 14:28:31','2013-12-17 14:28:31','<h2>Conference venue</h2>\r\nDay 1: <a title=\"Getting to STAM\" href=\"http://www.stamgent.be/en/visit/getting-there\" target=\"_blank\">STAM (located at the Bijloke site)</a> -  Day 2 &amp; 3: <a href=\"http://www.stamgent.be/en/visit/getting-there\">De Bijloke (nearby STAM, follow arrows \"Data Days 2014\")</a>\r\n<h2>Travel &amp; stay</h2>\r\n<h3>Hotels</h3>\r\nA list of hotel addresses and phone numbers is listed below.\r\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"235\"><strong>Hotel</strong></td>\r\n<td width=\"323\"><strong>Address</strong></td>\r\n<td width=\"129\"><strong>Telephone</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"235\"><a title=\"Ibis Ghent Opera hotel\" href=\"http://www.accorhotels.com/gb/hotel-1455-ibis-gent-centrum-opera/index.shtml\" target=\"_blank\">Ibis Gent Opera<strong>\r\n</strong></a></td>\r\n<td width=\"323\">Nederkouter 24</td>\r\n<td width=\"129\"> +32 9 225 07 07</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"235\"><a title=\"Monaterium hotel\" href=\"http://monasterium.be/index.php?taal=eng\" target=\"_blank\">Monasterium<strong>\r\n</strong></a></td>\r\n<td width=\"323\">Oude Houtlei 26</td>\r\n<td width=\"129\"> +32 9 269 22 10</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"235\"><a title=\"NH Hotel Gent Sint Pieters\" href=\"http://www.nh-hotels.com/nh/en/hotels/belgium/ghent/nh-gent-sint-pieters.html\" target=\"_blank\">NH Gent Sint Pieters<strong>\r\n</strong></a></td>\r\n<td width=\"323\">Koning Albertlaan 121</td>\r\n<td width=\"129\"> +32 9 222 60 65</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"235\"><a title=\"Sandton Grand Hotel Reylof\" href=\"http://www.sandton.eu/en/gent\" target=\"_blank\">Sandton Grand Hotel Reylof<strong>\r\n</strong></a></td>\r\n<td width=\"323\">Hoogstraat 36</td>\r\n<td width=\"129\"> +32 9 235 40 70</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"235\"><a title=\"Ibis Gent Kathedraal hotel\" href=\"http://www.accorhotels.com/gb/hotel-0961-ibis-gent-centrum-st-baafs-kathedraal/index.shtml\" target=\"_blank\">Ibis Gent Kathedraal<strong>\r\n</strong></a></td>\r\n<td width=\"323\">Limburgstraat 2</td>\r\n<td width=\"129\"> +32 9 293 90 00</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td width=\"235\"><a title=\"Ghent Marriott hotel\" href=\"http://www.marriott.com/hotels/hotel-photos/gnemc-ghent-marriott-hotel\" target=\"_blank\">Ghent Marriott<strong>\r\n</strong></a></td>\r\n<td width=\"323\">Korenlei 10</td>\r\n<td width=\"129\"> +32 9 233 93 93</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<h3>Air Travel</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Ghent is only 45 minutes from the<a title=\"Website Brussels Airport\" href=\"http://www.brusselsairport.be/en/\" target=\"_blank\"> <strong>international airport of Zaventem \'Brussel Airport\'</strong></a>, where flights arrive from and depart to more than 70 destinations. On the lowest level you will find the airport’s own railway station, Brussel-Nationaal-Luchthaven, accessible by lift and escalator from the arrivals hall. There are several train connections to Ghent from Brussel Airport.</li>\r\n	<li><a title=\"Charleroi Airport\" href=\"http://www.charleroi-airport.com/en/brussels-south-charleroi-airport/index.html\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Brussels South/Charleroi airport</strong></a> is 70 minutes from Ghent. There are more than 20 bus connections from the airport to the capital every day. From there frequent train connections to Ghent are available. There are also bus connections from the airport to Charleroi-Sud railway station. Trains for Ghent can also be boarded there. A ticket that combines the bus and train services can be purchased at the Airport Ticket Desk.</li>\r\n	<li>The <strong>other Belgian airports (<a title=\"Ostend Aerport\" href=\"http://www.ost.aero/en\" target=\"_blank\">Ostend</a>, <a title=\"Antwerp Airport\" href=\"http://www.antwerp-airport.be/contentpage_en.php\" target=\"_blank\">Antwerp </a>and <a title=\"Liege Airport\" href=\"http://www.liegeairport.com/en/home\" target=\"_blank\">Liège</a>)</strong> receive flights from various European cities and have easy direct connections to Ghent.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Ground Transportation and Parking</h2>\r\n<h3>Train</h3>\r\nGhent is easy to reach by train from all Belgian and European cities and is only half an hour from Brussels South Station. Thanks to the high-speed Eurostar and Thalys trains, you can travel from Ghent to Paris in barely 2 hours and to London, Amsterdam and Cologne in less than 3 hours.\r\nMore information at <a href=\"http://www.nmbs.be/\" target=\"_blank\">NMBS</a> ,<a href=\" http://www.thalys.be/ \" target=\"_blank\"> THALYS</a> and <a href=\" http://www.thalys.be\" target=\"_blank\">TGV</a>.\r\n<h3><strong>Taxis</strong></h3>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.visitghent.be/en/taxi?context=tourist\" target=\"_blank\">All information</a> about taxi transport. A single fare in Ghent city will cost 8,50 euro.\r\n<h3><strong>Bus Service</strong></h3>\r\nBus Service is widely available throughout Ghent. <a href=\"http://www.slimweg.be/toplocaties/debijloke.htm#bus\" target=\"_blank\">Bus travel schedule (Dutch)</a>\r\n<h3>Roadmap and Parking</h3>\r\nPlease visit <a href=\"http://www.slimweg.be/toplocaties/debijloke.htm\">slimweg.be</a> for information about driving to the conference public parkings. Please note that the nearest parking is <a href=\"http://www.mobiliteitgent.be/met-de-auto/ondergrondse-parkings/parking-sint-pietersplein-p10\" target=\"_blank\">parking \"Sint Pietersplein\"</a>.\r\n<h2>Information about Ghent</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.visitgent.be\">Practical information about the city of Ghent</a></li>\r\n	<li><a href=\"http://www.visitgent.be/en/winter-gent\"> Information about discovering Ghent in the winter</a></li>\r\n</ul>','Practical information','','publish','closed','open','','travelstay','','','2013-12-20 12:44:06','2013-12-20 12:44:06','',0,'http://www.datadays.eu/?page